  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When I deploy a miner node via puppeth, because RPC is not enabled, I am unable to propose a new miner - either by `clique.propose(address, authorized)` via the console (IPC endpoint is inside the container) or by `clique_propose` via RPC).\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have a prompt in the wizard which enables RPC while deploying a node.\r\n\r\nFrom what I can see, this requires a change in the Dockerfile here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/cmd/puppeth/module_node.go#L45 and a change in the wizard and nodeInfos structure.",
