    "body": "You can do that by SSHing into your remote machine, attaching it via docker and opening a console.\r\n\r\n```\r\nssh [...]\r\ndocker exec -it yournetwork_sealnode_1 /bin/sh\r\ngeth console\r\n```\r\n\r\nI know it's not nice, just a doable workaround for now",
